Input
Process
Output
Method Type 
Player can choose  upgrade screen or to move to character selection 
Mouse pressed function will check for collision between the mouse and the buttons
Either the code will load up the upgrade 
HomeScreen()
mousePressed()
Player Selecting Character option 
Checking for collision between mouse and character selection button 
The player will start the fight sequence using the character of their selection 
mousePressed()
Player presses the pausing button 
The pause code method will start and change the play boolean to create a pause and load the pause screen
The player will reach a screen that displays 2 options, continue playing the game or go back to the home screen. 
PausingGame()
mousePressed()
Player presses the R key therefore restarting the game 
The restart function will reset variables 
The player will restart the game starting from their first battle which will delete past progress.
RestartGame()
KeyPressed()


Player will choose to update a skill
The code will subtract some of the currency and add the rate in increase to that increased skill
The players character will have an increase in that skill
UpgradeScreen()
mousePressed()
Once the fights have been complete and the player presses next button
The code will use the levelUpdation method to increase the skills for the next opponent and reset needed variables 
The user will be brought to the next fight level
LevelUpdation()
mousePressed()


